    <h2>ILVE — Italian hand-assembly, Bassano del Grappa since 1953</h2>
    <p>ILVE Spa is a family-owned Italian luxury appliance manufacturer founded in 1953 in Bassano del Grappa, a town in Italy's Veneto region north of Venice. The Berto family has operated the company across multiple generations, maintaining independent family-ownership rather than being acquired by any of the major European or US appliance conglomerates. ILVE's manufacturing approach emphasizes hand-assembly — individual craftspeople at the Bassano del Grappa facility build each unit rather than running automated production lines. This hand-assembly approach is part of the brand's Italian artisan positioning and shows up in build quality + finish consistency that customers specifying ILVE are typically buying for.</p>
    <p>ILVE's 200+ color program is among the largest factory color selections in the luxury wall oven market. Colors range from mainstream finishes through signature Italian hues (Amalfi Red, Venezia Burgundy, Mediterraneo Blue, Toscana Gold among others) to custom-match options for specific hex values. For LA custom kitchens where the wall oven doubles as a design focal point, ILVE's color depth is a core differentiator. US distribution runs through Eurochef USA (Texas) — parts lead times 5-10 days on common service components, 7-14 days on specialty Italian parts.</p>
  </div></section>

