    <h2>60" side-by-side double wall oven — service implications</h2>
    <p>ILVE's 60" side-by-side double wall oven is a distinctive Italian configuration not commonly seen from US pro brands. Instead of the stacked upper-over-lower arrangement typical in 30" double wall ovens from Wolf, Viking, Thermador, or GE, ILVE's 60" places two separate ovens side by side in a 60" wide cabinet cutout. This drives specific service considerations:</p>
    <p><b>Each cavity is independent</b> — left and right ovens have their own bake elements, their own convection systems, their own temperature sensors. Failures concentrate in one cavity rather than taking out both simultaneously.</p>
    <p><b>Shared control panel</b> — the 60" unit shares a single control panel coordinating both cavities. Control-panel failures can affect both halves even when mechanicals are intact.</p>
    <p><b>Cabinet cutout considerations</b> — the 60" width requires specific cabinet planning; retrofit installations from a 30" to a 60" require cabinetry work that's beyond appliance-repair scope.</p>
    <p><b>LA install base</b> — 60" ILVE appears at larger custom kitchens in Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, and Hollywood Hills where the cabinet run accommodates the wider configuration.</p>
    <p><b>Per-cavity service</b> — one cavity's element or sensor failure doesn't affect the other; service at standard per-cavity pricing ($420-$780 typical).</p>
  </div></section>

